<br>
One facet of the game that is ever present is that some quests require a coordinated effort by as few as six and as many as thirty-six to accomplish.  I hope that we can help people do this, but we need to be careful that we don't overlook balance in what/how we do things.  I mean that on two levels:<br>
<br>
On one level, we need to do events for fun that are for as many in the guild as we can cover at one time.<br>
<br>
On another, we need to try to start coordinating raids which can help people complete quests.  One facet of raids is that they will tend to be exclusive - not all levels can attend and some people may not want to attend because of faction issues.  Also, raids which aid a few members must always be considered a voluntary activity.<br>
<br>
In the recent past, we've been very lax at accomplishing the first goal - events.  As such, member initiated raids have become the only guild events which have been occuring. As an officer, I feel some responsibility for our collective failure in this regard.  We (as a guild) need to start working on event type guild functions.  So to that end, think on the issue and be prepared to talk about things we can do to get that more coordinated.<br>
<br>
Have fun!<br>
<br>
