<br>
Also something to work on as we gain in levels and abilities is coordination between multiple groups at once. Our hunt in Mistmoore was the first time some of us have had to coordinate efforts with a number larger than a group of six...personally, I think we did very well for our first time out. Having Forin and I be the designated tanks for our groups and my message of &quot;Pulling 2, assist your team Dwarf&quot; helped also I think..heh. We had some difficulty finding a place to hunt and we had an initial wipeout when we first entered but none of us got flustered and quit. We simply picked up our rotting corpses and went back to the hunt. Very commendable.<br>
<br>
As we as a guild raise in levels and hopefully recruit more to add to our ranks, working as a team will become even more important. It makes me feel good to see the wolves that are close in level hunting together for individual or mutual benefit. It helps us develop an idea of the style that your packmate presents in combat and allows you to act in tandem with them. A prime example of this is Forin and I. We have known eachother for 22 of my levels and a year of time...those who know us make the occasional passing joke of the twin Dwarves, but our playing style only adds to that. When I engage a target with Forin at my side I know what is going to happen in combat, and there is very little chance for surprise (other than a mutual LoH on Kassandria in Permafrost, heh). Hopefully this will continue to happen with the rest of you, and I forsee that it will...<br>
<br>
Anyway, enough ranting. I'm late to get back from my break.<br>
<br>
See you tonight,<br>
